public1private2 = function(x){
  x = as.integer(x)
  case_when(
    x == 1 ~ "public",
    x == 2 ~ "private",
    TRUE ~ NA_character_) %>% as.factor()
}

2 Curating each data

Since the column names of each of the data are not consistent as of 16 May 2020, ref commit 96a1d8c55c5f17b22526e8e68c0bfd30799911eb, I will load each data by itself, clean and assemble at the end.

See the Google Sheet for the commonly agreed variables.

clean_2000 = sch_2000 %>% dplyr::transmute(
  country = cnt %>% as.factor(),
  school_id = schoolid %>% as.character(),
  fund_gov = sc04q01 %>% as.numeric(),
  fund_fees = sc04q02 %>% as.numeric(),
  fund_donation = sc04q03 %>% as.numeric(),
  enrol_boys = sc02q01 %>% as.numeric(),
  enrol_girls = sc02q02 %>% as.numeric(),
  stratio = stratio %>% as.numeric(),
  public_private = sc03q01 %>% public1private2(),
  staff_shortage = tcshort %>% as.numeric(),
  sch_wgt = wnrschbw %>% as.numeric(),
  school_size = schlsize %>% as.numeric())

clean_2003 = sch_2003 %>% dplyr::transmute(
  country = country_iso3c %>% as.factor(),
  school_id = school_id %>% as.character(),
  fund_gov = funding_gov %>% as.numeric() %>% na_if(997) %>% na_if(998) %>% na_if(999),
  fund_fees = funding_fees %>% as.numeric() %>% na_if(997) %>% na_if(998) %>% na_if(999),
  fund_donation = funding_donations %>% as.numeric() %>% na_if(997) %>% na_if(998) %>% na_if(999),
  enrol_boys = enrolment_boys %>% as.numeric(),
  enrol_girls = enrolment_girls %>% as.numeric(),
  stratio = student_teacher_ratio %>% as.numeric() %>% na_if(997) %>% na_if(998) %>% na_if(999),
  public_private = public_private %>% public1private2(),
  staff_shortage = staff_shortage %>% as.numeric() %>% na_if(997) %>% na_if(998) %>% na_if(999),
  sch_wgt = sch_wgt %>% as.numeric(),
  school_size = school_size %>% as.numeric() %>% na_if(99997) %>% na_if(99998) %>% na_if(99999))

3 Binding data

# Ensure all datasets have the same type for school_id and public_private before binding (converting to character)
list_data <- lst(clean_2000, clean_2003, clean_2006, clean_2009, clean_2012, clean_2015, clean_2018, clean_2022)

# Remove "clean_" from the names
names(list_data) <- names(list_data) %>% str_remove("clean_")

# Convert both school_id and public_private to character in each dataset to avoid type conflicts
list_data <- list_data %>%
  map(~ .x %>% 
        mutate(
          public_private = as.character(public_private)  # Convert public_private to character
        ))

# Bind the rows and convert character columns to factors
school <- list_data %>%
  bind_rows(.id = "year") %>%
  dplyr::mutate(
    year = as.integer(year), 
    public_private = as.factor(public_private)) %>%  # Convert public_private back to factor
  as_tibble()

5 Creating heatmap for README

# Summarize missingness for each column by year
missing_summary <- school %>%
  group_by(year) %>%                                  
  summarize(across(everything(),                   
                   ~ sum(is.na(.)) / n(),          
                   .names = "missing_{col}")) %>%  
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("missing_"),
               names_to = "column", 
               values_to = "missing_percentage") %>%
  mutate(column = str_remove(column, "missing_"),
         label_missing_percentage = scales::percent(missing_percentage, accuracy = 0.1)) 

# View the summary
missing_summary
## # A tibble: 96 × 4
##     year column         missing_percentage label_missing_percentage
##    <int> <chr>                       <dbl> <chr>                   
##  1  2000 country                    0      0.0%

##  3  2000 fund_gov                   0.0787 7.9%

##  6  2000 enrol_boys                 0.197  19.7%

## 10  2000 staff_shortage             0.0489 4.9%

p = missing_summary %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = factor(year), 
             y = column, 
             label = label_missing_percentage,
             fill = missing_percentage)) +
  geom_tile() +
  geom_text() +
  scale_fill_gradient2(
    low = "white", 
    high = "#287afc",
    breaks = c(0, 0.5, 1),
    labels = scales::label_percent()) +
  labs(title = "Missingness Percentage in the School Data by Variables and Year",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Variables", 
       fill = "Missing Percentage") +
  scale_x_discrete(breaks = c(2000, 2003, 2006, 2009, 2012, 2015, 2018, 2022)) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")

print(p)

ggsave(plot = p, 
       filename = here("Data/Output/Transfer/README_school_data_missing_values_summary.png"), height = 6, width = 12)
